proctoru is a live online proctoring service for students taking exams online. proctoru uses a three-step process to replicate the face-to-face proctoring experience over the internet to ensure academic integrity in sjsu's online courses. this service is only available to courses that are taught . this is verified by the course mode as noted on mysjsu (modes: 1,2,10). proctoru is only for use for high stakes exams, such as midterms and final exams. please contact ecampus@sjsu.edu if you are interested in using proctoru or have any questions related to proctoru. how it works - test taker [pdf] student walk-through video technical requirements pre-exam checklist [pdf] how it works - faculty [pdf] instructor account creation [pdf] faq's [pdf] download adobe reader phone: 408-924-2337 email: ecampus@sjsu.edu location: irc, room 206 ecampus, irc206 instructional resource center san jose state university one washington square san jose, ca 95192-0026 